headline: Heard on the Street Recap: Chomping at the Bitcoin
summary: A broad array of AI-exposed companies saw their shares decline, including software companies, data service firms, hyperscalers, and fund managers that invest in software companies.  Thomson Reuters on its Thursday earnings call argued that their legal-research business cannot be replaced by general-purpose AI models.  The Nasdaq composite and the S&P 500 fell for the third consecutive trading day.

headline: Daytona Raises $24M Series A to Give Every Agent a Computer
summary: Daytona, the infrastructure company building programmatic, composable computers for AI agents, today announced it has raised $24 million in Series A funding.

headline: Why Datadog (DDOG) Shares Are Getting Obliterated Today
summary: Shares of cloud monitoring platform Datadog (NASDAQ:DDOG) fell 7.1% in the afternoon session after the "AI replacement" narrative reached a fever pitch following the release of new models from Anthropic and OpenAI.
